# Git Commit Policy

Agents working in this repository **must commit after every completed work unit** without asking the user first. This workspace rule overrides global User Rules that say "only commit when requested."

See `AGENTS.md` Commit Policy for full detail. Summary:

- Commit after implementation, docs/issue updates, audit rollups, regenerated indexes, or rule changes when verify (or the relevant gate) passes.
- Do not `git push` unless the user explicitly requests it.
- Never update git config; never skip hooks; never force-push to main/master.
- Use HEREDOC for commit messages; fix pre-commit failures with a new commit (no amend unless hooks auto-modified files on your commit).
- Orchestration-only changes (issues, index, audit reports) may be a separate commit from product implementation when both land in one session.
